<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Raymond Burr, who plays TV's quintessential TV lawyer Perry Mason, will 
venture into syndicated television for the first time this fall as host of a 
daily, half-hour series dramatizing court cases. The dick clark production is 
called "Trial by Jury." ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
